## Session 2026-07-07 (cont.) — Chapter 2: deterministic routing + cross-collection composition

### Tier 1.5 — concept-centroid routing (chat)
Dry-run on 8 eval questions justified it: centroid similarity ranked the right collection in 5-6/8, including three the Tier 2 LLM was failing (PP-06, DL-07, XC-05). Implemented in `select_collections`: one question embedding vs ALL collections' concept-vector centroids (single pgvector SQL); when the leader clears `centroid_routing.min_sim` (0.6), collections within `margin` (0.08) are selected (max 3) and **the Tier 2 LLM call is skipped entirely** — deterministic routing + one less LLM call per turn (SPEED-01's first win). Murky cases fall through to the LLM exactly as before. Tier 1 anchors merge in and are never dropped by the cap. Verified: PP-06 ✅ (was ❌), DL-07 chat ✅ (was ❌), DL-08 held, multi 18/18.
Twins bonus: kb/obsidian centroid scores sit adjacent (0.769/0.775) so top-3 naturally includes both; the fan-out's best-answer pick arbitrates.

### Tier 1.25 — identifier-prefix anchors (chat)
Question content words (config noise lists excluded) that prefix-match a collection's **identifier column** pin that collection like a filename does ('jpm' -> jpm_cfd_position, 'citi' -> citi_dcm_fees.csv). identifier column ONLY — matching primary_name routed xml via 'check' -> CheckSum during calibration.

### Cross-collection composition (XC bucket structural gap — closed)
Raed's design, better than the LLM-context merge first proposed: **compose, don't blend.** Runner-up STRUCTURED answers (records/metadata only — never a second procedure doc, which invites step-blending; see PR-03 💀) are appended verbatim AFTER synthesis as "**From {collection}:**" blocks — the LLM never sees them, zero contamination. Doc runner-ups remain related links. Includes the "No exact match — closest results" record listings (that's where the file lists live). Relevance gate: a question word must be the PREFIX of a LISTED IDENTIFIER — names/descriptions excluded ('check' in 'CheckSum', 'date' in a field description = coincidence, not evidence). Router fixes en route: the no-exact-match branch now sets `_last_answer_payload` (was unclassifiable downstream) and `_last_answer_payload` resets per call (stale-payload leak across questions — latent cross-link-enrichment bug).
**Verified: XC-02 ✅ (procedure + jpm records + 090_W_RECON_JPM_PB_PULL), XC-05 ✅ (workflow + citi file records), bbg/xml noise gated out, single-item + multi 18/18 unaffected.**

### Lesson (paid for twice tonight)
Loose string matchers MULTIPLY: a prefix-match on names ('check'->CheckSum) routed noise in, and a substring gate ('check' ⊂ 'checksum') waved it through. Identifier-anchored, prefix-only matching composed cleanly on the first try. If a deterministic guard needs a third refinement round, disable it behind config and take it to the design board.

